      • getEvents

        public JsonData getEvents(long lastRowId,
                          int limit)
        Fetches Events whose rowid > #lastRowId up to the #limit provided. Each jsonObject contains the default properties as the one fetched from the DB with an additional property that holds the syncStatus and rowid which are used for peer-to-peer sync.
        Parameters:
        lastRowId -
        Returns:
        JsonData which contains a JSONArray and the maximum row id in the array of Events returned. This enables this method to be called again for the consequent batches

      • getClients

        public JsonData getClients(long lastRowId,
                           int limit)
        Fetches Clients whose rowid > #lastRowId up to the #limit provided.
        Parameters:
        lastRowId -
        Returns:
        JsonData which contains a JSONArray and the maximum row id in the array of Clients returned or null if no records match the conditions or an exception occurred. This enables this method to be called again for the consequent batches
